ionship that establishes it first.', 290, 0), (220737, 'I''m still shy," I admit, pulling the sleeves over my hands, "and I might always be, I don''t know, but I think you can be shy and still feel okay about yourself at the same time.', 14729, 0), (220738, 'The one person you''ll be spending the rest of your life with is you. Treat yourself with love and respect.', 25690, 0), (220739, 'Because we were treated neglectfully and abusively in our young years—when we most needed self-love to be mirrored—it was difficult to hold onto…We take up the challenge of learning to love ourselves, through our highs & our lows, when we are finding acceptance from others and when we are being closed out and rejected.', 14778, 0), (220740, 'Each and every Indian, man or woman, child or Elder, is a spirit-warrior.', 39431, 0), (220741, 'I''m safe inside this container called me.', 48, 0), (220742, 'I can be a better me than anyone can', 39432, 0), (220743, 'May you always remember the Beloved is your divine and sacred self.', 19403, 0), (220744, 'No one observed and beheld me, I observed and beheld myself; the invisible current went out and it came back to me. I came to love myself out of defiance, out of despair, because there was nothing else. Such a love will do, but it will only do, it is not the best kind; it has the taste of something left out on a shelf too long that has turned rancid, and when eaten makes the stomach turn. It will do, it will do, but only because there is nothing else to take its place; it is not to be recommended.', 4293, 0), (220745, 'I know who I am.', 2878, 0), (220746, 'Celebrate every moment of your sacred-life.', 2878, 0), (220747, 'every time you tell your daughteryou yell at herout of loveyou teach her to confuseanger with kindnesswhich seems like a good ideatill she grows up totrust men who hurt hercause they look so muchlike you- to fathers with daughters', 694, 0), (220748, 'i don''t blame you for not knowing how to remain soft with me. sometimes 